cs.AI, cs.GT, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.SI 

This paper is about creating poker-playing programs using Nash equilibrium approximation, which falls under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the quality of the approximation, which could fall under machine learning (cs.LG) or cryptography and security (cs.CR) if the evaluation involves analyzing the security of the program. Finally, the paper proposes a new method for computing an approximate lower bound, which could fall under social and information networks (cs.SI) as it involves analyzing the behavior of players in a game.
